steps.description:
Apply the changes from PR #23932 which introduced the new `Object(<schema_format>)` data type for semi-structured data. This type supports storing JSON data where all paths are automatically extracted and written as separate columns in optimal types. Subcolumns can be queried by path names (e.g., `data.key1.key2`) or with the cast operator (e.g., `data.key1.key2::Int64`).
```sql
CREATE TABLE example (data Object('JSON')) ENGINE = MergeTree ORDER BY tuple();
INSERT INTO example FORMAT JSONEachRow {"data": {"name": "John", "age": 42, "location": {"country": "USA", "city": "New York"}}};
SELECT data.name, data.location.city FROM example;
```
